{
  "texts": [
    "The patient's baseline liver function tests were within normal limits, with an Alanine Aminotransferase (ALT) level of 45 IU/L (normal range: 30-45 IU/L).",
    "However, upon re-evaluation 4 weeks post-treatment initiation, her ALT levels had markedly elevated to 1123 IU/L.",
    "Should the prescribed HCV treatment be discontinued in light of this significant ALT elevation?",
    "Two expert hepatologists drafted 20 questions that specifically refer to information about management recommendations addressing information contained in the guideline main text (10 questions), graphical tables (5 questions), and clinical scenarios (5 questions).",
    "https://doi.org/10.1038/s41746-024-01091-y explanation see Supplementary Note 2)."
  ]
}